    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p><b>Given :</b> $x(t)=10 \\cos (10.5 \\mathrm{Wt})$</p>\n\n<p>$$ h(t)=\\pi\\left(\\frac{\\sin W t}{\\pi t}\\right)^2 \\cos (10 \\mathrm{Wt}) $$</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyxdk6ti/63b8b58e-c38e-4b35-90e8-777539172509/de668b50-485f-11ef-8807-81b9920dce91/file-jaoe38c1lyxdk6tj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyxdk6ti/63b8b58e-c38e-4b35-90e8-777539172509/de668b50-485f-11ef-8807-81b9920dce91/file-jaoe38c1lyxdk6tj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Signals and Systems - Transmission of Signal Through Continuous Time LTI Systems Question 1 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyxdn324/1c5eff96-ded4-4a57-abdc-8744ed141473/2eec67c0-4860-11ef-8807-81b9920dce91/file-jaoe38c1lyxdn325.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyxdn324/1c5eff96-ded4-4a57-abdc-8744ed141473/2eec67c0-4860-11ef-8807-81b9920dce91/file-jaoe38c1lyxdn325.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Signals and Systems - Transmission of Signal Through Continuous Time LTI Systems Question 1 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyxdmzgh/d40f0789-6da6-402e-8c64-a8df27495844/2c244710-4860-11ef-8807-81b9920dce91/file-jaoe38c1lyxdmzgi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyxdmzgh/d40f0789-6da6-402e-8c64-a8df27495844/2c244710-4860-11ef-8807-81b9920dce91/file-jaoe38c1lyxdmzgi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Signals and Systems - Transmission of Signal Through Continuous Time LTI Systems Question 1 English Explanation 3\">\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyxdmw2f/073d1ab8-2f04-47af-bac0-2dccf1ee8996/2985f580-4860-11ef-8807-81b9920dce91/file-jaoe38c1lyxdmw2g.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyxdmw2f/073d1ab8-2f04-47af-bac0-2dccf1ee8996/2985f580-4860-11ef-8807-81b9920dce91/file-jaoe38c1lyxdmw2g.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Signals and Systems - Transmission of Signal Through Continuous Time LTI Systems Question 1 English Explanation 4\">\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; |H(10.5 \\mathrm{~W})|=\\frac{1.5 \\mathrm{~W}}{4} \\text { and } \\angle H(10.5 \\mathrm{~W})=0^{\\circ} \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\therefore  y(t)=|H(10.5 \\mathrm{~W})| x(t) \\\\\\\\ &amp; y(t)=\\frac{1.5 \\mathrm{~W}}{4} \\times 10 \\cos (10.5 \\mathrm{Wt})=\\frac{15 \\mathrm{~W}}{4} \\cos (10.5 \\mathrm{Wt}) \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (A).</p>",
